encyclopedia.content: Fender公司(目前还没有一个比较官方的中文名字，但大多数音乐人都习惯称其为“芬达”或“芬德”）于1946年建立，全称Fender Musical Instruments Corporation，在过去的50年中，Fender已经成为了美国的标志之一，Fender对现代音乐音色发展的贡献波及全球并且仍在继续。通过率先推出商业化的实心电吉他、生产出第一把电贝斯以及难以数记的经典音箱，Fender乐器已经在爵士、布鲁斯、乡村、摇滚等等许多流行音乐风格上留下了印记。

entry.def: A fender is a low metal wall built around a fireplace, which stops any coals that fall out of the fire from rolling onto the carpet.
A fender is the same as a fireguard .
The fenders of a car are the parts of the body over the wheels.
The fender of a car is a bar at the front or back that protects the car if it bumps into something.
The fenders of a boat are objects which hang against the outside and protect it from damage when it comes next to a harbour wall or another boat.
